{
    "level": "A1–B1",
    "intro": "In this section you will learn <strong>basic grammar</strong> of the English language: word order in a sentence, interrogative and negative structures, adverbs and circumstances.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "Word order",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "Basic structure <strong>S–V–O</strong> — subject, verb, object:",
            "example": "She reads books every day."
        },
        {
            "label": "Questions",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "Auxiliary verb <strong>do/does/did</strong> before the subject:",
            "example": "Do you like pizza?"
        },
        {
            "label": "Negation",
            "color": "rose",
            "text": "We use <strong>do/does/did + not</strong>:",
            "example": "I don't like apples."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. The main elements of a sentence",
    "intro": "An English sentence is built according to a clear structure:",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Subject",
            "title": "Subject (S)",
            "subtitle": "Who performs the action: I, you, she, Tom"
        },
        {
            "label": "Verb",
            "title": " (V)",
            "subtitle": "Action or state: read, eat, is, have"
        },
        {
            "label": "Object",
            "title": "Appendix (O)",
            "subtitle": "To whom/what the action is directed: book, coffee"
        },
        {
            "label": "Adverbials",
            "title": "Circumstances",
            "subtitle": "When, where, how: yesterday, at home, quickly"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Sentence types",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Affirmative",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "Basic S–V–O structure without additional elements.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "She reads books.",
                    "ua": "Вона читає книги."
                },
                {
                    "en": "They play football.",
                    "ua": "Вони грають у футбол."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Питальні",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "Допоміжне дієслово <strong>do/does/did</strong> на початку.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Do you like pizza?",
                    "ua": "Do you like pizza?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Does she work here?",
                    "ua": "She works here?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Negative",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "Add <strong>not</strong> after the auxiliary verbs.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "I don't like coffee.",
                    "ua": "I don't like coffee."
                },
                {
                    "en": "She doesn't work here.",
                    "ua": "She doesn't work here."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Key rules",
    "items": [
        "Basic structure: <strong>S + V + O</strong> (subject + verb + object).",
        "Adverbs of frequency (<em>always, often, never</em>) - <strong>before the main verb</strong>.",
        "Circumstances of time and place - usually <strong>at the end</strong> sentence.",
        "The order of circumstances: <strong>Manner → Place → Time</strong>.",
        "In questions, the auxiliary verb <strong>before the subject</strong>."
    ]
}
